    "result": {"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Haiku Docs"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"0e241de7-51d2-5537-9008-d45196dfc836","excerpt":"Do you know the difference between  and ? When should you use the one over the other?  When using  the container element acts like a block level element. Theâ€¦","html":"<p>Do you know the difference between <code class=\"language-text\">display:flex</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">display:inline-flex</code>? When should you use the one over the other?</p>\n<h2><code class=\"language-text\">display:flex</code></h2>\n<p>When using <code class=\"language-text\">display:flex</code> the container element acts like a block level element. The flex container element is as wide as its parent container (the blue background is the flex container element).</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/052f3e0fe1d017c5886003a2a66f71ae/2215f/display-flex.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 15.18987341772152%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"example of display:flex being used.\"\n        title=\"example of display:flex being used.\"\n        src=\"/static/052f3e0fe1d017c5886003a2a66f71ae/f058b/display-flex.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/052f3e0fe1d017c5886003a2a66f71ae/c26ae/display-flex.png 158w,\n/static/052f3e0fe1d017c5886003a2a66f71ae/6bdcf/display-flex.png 315w,\n/static/052f3e0fe1d017c5886003a2a66f71ae/f058b/display-flex.png 630w,\n/static/052f3e0fe1d017c5886003a2a66f71ae/40601/display-flex.png 945w,\n/static/052f3e0fe1d017c5886003a2a66f71ae/78612/display-flex.png 1260w,\n/static/052f3e0fe1d017c5886003a2a66f71ae/2215f/display-flex.png 1548w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<deckgo-highlight-code language=\"css\"  >\n          <code slot=\"code\">.parent {\r\n  /* \r\n    currently not visible due to the flex container element \r\n    rendering as a block element \r\n  */\r\n  background-color: yellow;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n  width: 300px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex {\r\n  display: flex;\r\n  flex-direction: row;\r\n  background-color: lightblue;\r\n  padding: 8px;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex &gt; * {\r\n  border: 1px solid black;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n  margin-right: 8px;\r\n  padding: 8px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex &gt; *:last-child {\r\n  margin-right: 0;\r\n}</code>\n        </deckgo-highlight-code>\n<h2><code class=\"language-text\">display:inline-flex</code></h2>\n<p>When using <code class=\"language-text\">display:inline-flex</code> the flex container element acts like an inline level element. The flex container element is <strong>only</strong> as wide as its child elements (the yellow background is the parent container element, the blue background is the flex container element).</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/c3d4cffa04ae554dceb40c38c6390d95/2215f/display-inline-flex.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 12.658227848101264%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"example of display:inline-flex being used.\"\n        title=\"example of display:inline-flex being used.\"\n        src=\"/static/c3d4cffa04ae554dceb40c38c6390d95/f058b/display-inline-flex.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/c3d4cffa04ae554dceb40c38c6390d95/c26ae/display-inline-flex.png 158w,\n/static/c3d4cffa04ae554dceb40c38c6390d95/6bdcf/display-inline-flex.png 315w,\n/static/c3d4cffa04ae554dceb40c38c6390d95/f058b/display-inline-flex.png 630w,\n/static/c3d4cffa04ae554dceb40c38c6390d95/40601/display-inline-flex.png 945w,\n/static/c3d4cffa04ae554dceb40c38c6390d95/78612/display-inline-flex.png 1260w,\n/static/c3d4cffa04ae554dceb40c38c6390d95/2215f/display-inline-flex.png 1548w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<deckgo-highlight-code language=\"css\"  >\n          <code slot=\"code\">.parent {\r\n  background-color: yellow;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n  width: 300px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex {\r\n  display: inline-flex;\r\n  flex-direction: row;\r\n  background-color: lightblue;\r\n  padding: 8px;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex &gt; * {\r\n  border: 1px solid black;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n  margin-right: 8px;\r\n  padding: 8px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex &gt; *:last-child {\r\n  margin-right: 0;\r\n}</code>\n        </deckgo-highlight-code>\n<p>When using <code class=\"language-text\">display:inline-flex</code> you can have two flex container elements side by side if the parent container is wide enough.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b467bd425304abfd289393e570123378/fe60e/display-inline-flex-multiple-row.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 11.39240506329114%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"example of display:inline-flex being used with multiple flex containers side by side.\"\n        title=\"example of display:inline-flex being used with multiple flex containers side by side.\"\n        src=\"/static/b467bd425304abfd289393e570123378/f058b/display-inline-flex-multiple-row.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b467bd425304abfd289393e570123378/c26ae/display-inline-flex-multiple-row.png 158w,\n/static/b467bd425304abfd289393e570123378/6bdcf/display-inline-flex-multiple-row.png 315w,\n/static/b467bd425304abfd289393e570123378/f058b/display-inline-flex-multiple-row.png 630w,\n/static/b467bd425304abfd289393e570123378/40601/display-inline-flex-multiple-row.png 945w,\n/static/b467bd425304abfd289393e570123378/78612/display-inline-flex-multiple-row.png 1260w,\n/static/b467bd425304abfd289393e570123378/fe60e/display-inline-flex-multiple-row.png 1677w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<deckgo-highlight-code language=\"css\"  >\n          <code slot=\"code\">.parent {\r\n  background-color: yellow;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n  width: 350px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex {\r\n  display: inline-flex;\r\n  flex-direction: row;\r\n  background-color: lightblue;\r\n  padding: 8px;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex &gt; * {\r\n  border: 1px solid black;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n  margin-right: 8px;\r\n  padding: 8px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex &gt; *:last-child {\r\n  margin-right: 0;\r\n}</code>\n        </deckgo-highlight-code>\n<p>If the parent element is not wide enough the second flex container element will move to a second line.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ede5f82d2c7a20172e5ad69475b72171/e8814/display-inline-flex-multiple-row-not-enough-width.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 30.37974683544304%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"example of display:inline-flex being used with multiple flex containers with not enough width to support both flex containers.\"\n        title=\"example of display:inline-flex being used with multiple flex containers with not enough width to support both flex containers.\"\n        src=\"/static/ede5f82d2c7a20172e5ad69475b72171/f058b/display-inline-flex-multiple-row-not-enough-width.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ede5f82d2c7a20172e5ad69475b72171/c26ae/display-inline-flex-multiple-row-not-enough-width.png 158w,\n/static/ede5f82d2c7a20172e5ad69475b72171/6bdcf/display-inline-flex-multiple-row-not-enough-width.png 315w,\n/static/ede5f82d2c7a20172e5ad69475b72171/f058b/display-inline-flex-multiple-row-not-enough-width.png 630w,\n/static/ede5f82d2c7a20172e5ad69475b72171/40601/display-inline-flex-multiple-row-not-enough-width.png 945w,\n/static/ede5f82d2c7a20172e5ad69475b72171/78612/display-inline-flex-multiple-row-not-enough-width.png 1260w,\n/static/ede5f82d2c7a20172e5ad69475b72171/e8814/display-inline-flex-multiple-row-not-enough-width.png 1392w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<deckgo-highlight-code language=\"css\"  >\n          <code slot=\"code\">.parent {\r\n  background-color: yellow;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n  width: 300px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex {\r\n  display: inline-flex;\r\n  flex-direction: row;\r\n  background-color: lightblue;\r\n  padding: 8px;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex:first-child {\r\n  margin-bottom: 8px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex &gt; * {\r\n  border: 1px solid black;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n  margin-right: 8px;\r\n  padding: 8px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex &gt; *:last-child {\r\n  margin-right: 0;\r\n}</code>\n        </deckgo-highlight-code>\n<p>When using <code class=\"language-text\">flex-direction:column</code> with <code class=\"language-text\">display:inline-flex</code> the flex container element will be as wide as the widest child element.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/1115ff0b4cf378d125fbfd4cd56490e2/2215f/display-inline-flex-direction-column.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 54.43037974683544%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"example of display:inline-flex in combination with flex-direaction:column showing that the parent flex container will grow as wide as the widest child element.\"\n        title=\"example of display:inline-flex in combination with flex-direaction:column showing that the parent flex container will grow as wide as the widest child element.\"\n        src=\"/static/1115ff0b4cf378d125fbfd4cd56490e2/f058b/display-inline-flex-direction-column.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/1115ff0b4cf378d125fbfd4cd56490e2/c26ae/display-inline-flex-direction-column.png 158w,\n/static/1115ff0b4cf378d125fbfd4cd56490e2/6bdcf/display-inline-flex-direction-column.png 315w,\n/static/1115ff0b4cf378d125fbfd4cd56490e2/f058b/display-inline-flex-direction-column.png 630w,\n/static/1115ff0b4cf378d125fbfd4cd56490e2/40601/display-inline-flex-direction-column.png 945w,\n/static/1115ff0b4cf378d125fbfd4cd56490e2/78612/display-inline-flex-direction-column.png 1260w,\n/static/1115ff0b4cf378d125fbfd4cd56490e2/2215f/display-inline-flex-direction-column.png 1548w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<deckgo-highlight-code language=\"css\"  >\n          <code slot=\"code\">.parent {\r\n  background-color: yellow;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n  width: 300px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex {\r\n  display: inline-flex;\r\n  flex-direction: column;\r\n  background-color: lightblue;\r\n  padding: 8px;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n  align-items: flex-start;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex &gt; * {\r\n  border: 1px solid black;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n  margin-bottom: 8px;\r\n  padding: 8px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex &gt; *:last-child {\r\n  margin-bottom: 0;\r\n}</code>\n        </deckgo-highlight-code>\n<p>You can also have <code class=\"language-text\">flex-direction:column</code> containers side by side when using <code class=\"language-text\">display:inline-flex</code></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/47beca7059306321c2c107121d67d457/5df5d/display-inline-flex-direction-column-side-by-side.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 53.16455696202532%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"example of display:inline-flex in combination with flex-direaction:column showing that flex containers can be rendered side by side.\"\n        title=\"example of display:inline-flex in combination with flex-direaction:column showing that flex containers can be rendered side by side.\"\n        src=\"/static/47beca7059306321c2c107121d67d457/f058b/display-inline-flex-direction-column-side-by-side.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/47beca7059306321c2c107121d67d457/c26ae/display-inline-flex-direction-column-side-by-side.png 158w,\n/static/47beca7059306321c2c107121d67d457/6bdcf/display-inline-flex-direction-column-side-by-side.png 315w,\n/static/47beca7059306321c2c107121d67d457/f058b/display-inline-flex-direction-column-side-by-side.png 630w,\n/static/47beca7059306321c2c107121d67d457/40601/display-inline-flex-direction-column-side-by-side.png 945w,\n/static/47beca7059306321c2c107121d67d457/78612/display-inline-flex-direction-column-side-by-side.png 1260w,\n/static/47beca7059306321c2c107121d67d457/5df5d/display-inline-flex-direction-column-side-by-side.png 1572w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<deckgo-highlight-code language=\"css\"  >\n          <code slot=\"code\">.parent {\r\n  background-color: yellow;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n  width: 300px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex {\r\n  display: inline-flex;\r\n  flex-direction: column;\r\n  background-color: lightblue;\r\n  padding: 8px;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex &gt; * {\r\n  border: 1px solid black;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n  margin-bottom: 8px;\r\n  padding: 8px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex &gt; *:last-child {\r\n  margin-bottom: 0;\r\n}</code>\n        </deckgo-highlight-code>\n<p>Your inline flex container elements can still render below one another instead of being rendered side by side if the parent container element is not wide enough to fit all the flex container elements side by side.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3ee1fa169bbf57681031b38df01dcb25/f058b/display-inline-flex-direction-column-being-stacked.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 90.50632911392405%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"example of display:inline-flex in combination with flex-direaction:column showing that flex containers will still render below one another if the parent container element is not wide enough to rendere the inline flex container elements side by side.\"\n        title=\"example of display:inline-flex in combination with flex-direaction:column showing that flex containers will still render below one another if the parent container element is not wide enough to rendere the inline flex container elements side by side.\"\n        src=\"/static/3ee1fa169bbf57681031b38df01dcb25/f058b/display-inline-flex-direction-column-being-stacked.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/3ee1fa169bbf57681031b38df01dcb25/c26ae/display-inline-flex-direction-column-being-stacked.png 158w,\n/static/3ee1fa169bbf57681031b38df01dcb25/6bdcf/display-inline-flex-direction-column-being-stacked.png 315w,\n/static/3ee1fa169bbf57681031b38df01dcb25/f058b/display-inline-flex-direction-column-being-stacked.png 630w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<deckgo-highlight-code language=\"css\"  >\n          <code slot=\"code\">.parent {\r\n  background-color: yellow;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n  width: 150px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex {\r\n  display: inline-flex;\r\n  flex-direction: column;\r\n  background-color: lightblue;\r\n  padding: 8px;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex:first-child {\r\n  margin-bottom: 8px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex &gt; * {\r\n  border: 1px solid black;\r\n  border-radius: 8px;\r\n  margin-bottom: 8px;\r\n  padding: 8px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.flex &gt; *:last-child {\r\n  margin-bottom: 0;\r\n}</code>\n        </deckgo-highlight-code>","frontmatter":{"title":"display:flex vs display:inline flex","date":"October 23, 2021","description":"Learn the difference between display:flex and inline-flex"}},"previous":null,"next":null},"pageContext":{"id":"0e241de7-51d2-5537-9008-d45196dfc836","previousPostId":null,"nextPostId":null}},
